Chapter 1
Cohren
0430 Itania-Time. Cohren hated waking up so early. He hated it above all because he was responsible for waking up everyone else in his platoon.
He pulled out a lighter from one jacket pocket and a cigarette from the other. He lit it and took a quick drag, before opening the door a bit. In the past week, he had had to come up with quite a few tricks to wake up the men and women under his command. He no longer used the pre-set alarm, as it usually didn't work and all he got was a faint buzzing from the speakers.
"Wake them up?" Cohren turned around and saw Sergeant Nemic approaching him.
"Yes," replied Cohren.
"What are you going to try this time?"
Before he could answer, the door opened and Harris, Craith, and a few others were already approaching him in full uniform.
"Good morning," said Craith.
"What have you woken up to?" asked Cohren.
"So, first of all, we didn't feel like waiting to see what you'd come up with again today. And secondly, the advance troops, who are the first to rise, get to pick the morning ration," replied one of the men, Ravik. "And you know how bad the food can be, anyway."
"Good point, Sergeant," said Cohren. He reached in and flipped a switch. A loud, high-pitched alarm blared from the barracks. Inside, he heard muffled curses and people scrambling around.
"Come on, Valtori," said Nemic. "You'd think they'd have learned by now to wake up at the same time as you."
"Well, my guys from the training camp have learned it," Cohren replied, nodding towards Harris, Craith, and Ravik. "But, of course, the squad and platoon leaders also know that they need to get up before their units."
Seconds later, the rest of the company emerged. They had everything they needed, from personal items to necessary equipment. Some of the newer recruits looked bewildered, while others seemed annoyed.
"Good morning," said Cohren cheerfully.
"Why must you wake us up like this, Sergeant?" asked a sergeant of the advance troops.
"Because regular alarms are crap and Daybreak doesn't sleep," said Cohren.
"Pack up all your personal gear," Cohren continued. As a lieutenant colonel and the executive officer of the company, he was responsible for overseeing and supporting the company with the company commander, Captain Boradin Shaw. "We're not coming back here. Sergeants and lieutenants, you and your teams have 15 minutes for the final checks and to pack the daily rations."
The members of the Exodus Company scattered quickly. They were part of the second advance troops division, second army. Before they were consolidated, they were two companies, Cohort and Dagger. The company was split, and that was the main reason why Cohren had mixed feelings about his promotion to lieutenant colonel.
Cohren and Nemic, the leader of the first platoon, walked side by side in the glow of the many generator-powered lamps of the forward operational base. Most had red-tinted glass to avoid being detected by enemy bombers. Daybreak had resorted to Wild Weasel attacks from the air and ground to counter them.
"Another day and a new task for the Hellhounds," said Nemic with a dry laugh. "Where are they sending us?"
"An advanced operational base outside of Ianlos. We'll be supporting the ground attack," Cohren replied, taking a drag on his cigarette. He gave Craith a partial blame for starting him on smoking, but a year in the field changed a man, so he said nothing.
"Shit. It's getting worse at the front," muttered Nemic. "All the news is saying: 'Support the war efforts. Send aid to the Kurgan front.' How about some help for the Howland front?"
"Amen, brother," Cohren said, flicking the remains of his cigarette into the mud. "At least we're going out with the first armed platoon and won't have to run. Captain Shaw should be there by now."
"Captain Shaw cleared a ride for us?" Nemic asked a bit surprised.
"Yes, he's not as bad as I thought. Not particularly easy to get along with, but you can manage with him."
Cohren raised his index and middle fingers to his throat microphone, while putting on his backpack. "All units of the Exodus Company are to meet at West Vehicle Park when ready. We'll break out with the first armed platoon at 0500."
In the seconds that followed, he received responses from the squad leaders. Harris, Craith, and Ravik were all low-ranking non-commissioned officers when they first arrived here. The four had been close friends since their return to Earth, despite having known each other for only a couple of years. Cohren felt like he'd known them forever, although it was probably just over two years. They were all squad leaders, although Craith had been leading the second platoon for a week, after the previous leader was medically discharged following a Daybreak sniper's wound.
On their way to the vehicle park, Cohren and Nemic spotted a group of about eight Kronos combat tanks and four infantry fighting vehicles. Their crews were milling around, making sure their machines were combat-ready. Cohren quickly spotted Captain Boradin Shaw, who was talking to the commander of the armed platoon. As they approached, Shaw looked over at them and walked towards them, as always with a blank expression.
"Lieutenant Nemic... Lieutenant Valtori... He said Cohren was slower, glancing at Cohren's pistol holster and then back up again. "The company is ready, I presume?"
